@Node Introduction "Introduction"

  Introduction
  ============

    Small CLI tool to give you info about an icon
    also lets you un-snapshot icons.

@EndNode

@Node Requirements "Requirements"

  Requirements
  ============

    An Amiga with kickstart 3.0 or better (see notes)
    Some Icons :-)

    Notes:
      I wrote this program on an A4000T with WB3.1 and have
      not tested it on any other systems except my A3000 also with 3.1
      It should work down to 3.0 and maybe 2.04.  If it does could someone
      e-mail @{"me" link Author} and let me know please.

@EndNode

@Node Installation "Installation"

  Installation
  ============

    Use the supplied installer script or follow the procedure below.

    Manual Installation
    ===================

    Copy the files "IconTool" and "IconTool.Guide" using the
    workbench to a folder of your choice.

    That's it.

@EndNode

@Node Usage "Usage"

  Usage
  =====

    Open a CLI prompt and change to where you installed the program
    (or any other directory if you installed it in the path)

    Type in

    IconTool

    and press return for the usage.

    You can get info or unsnapshot on one or more icons at a time
    by specifying them on the command line.

    Don't specify the .info part of the filename

    You can use the QUIET switch to keep output to a minimum.
    
    You can override the TYPE of an icon.
    
    Examples:          
    ---------
    
      Create a new drawer in "RAM:" called "Test", make sure the file
      "RAM:Test.info" exists and try the following:
    
      IconTool RAM:Test INFO

      IconTool RAM:Test UNSNAPSHOT

      IconTool RAM:Test TYPE=PROJECT

      IconTool RAM:Test TYPE=DRAWER INFO UNSNAPSHOT
    
@EndNode

@Node Distribution "Distribution"

  Distribution
  ============

    This program may be included on BBS's, Web Sites, Archive Sites (e.g.
    Aminet) and any storage media you like (even punch tape :-)

    If you add this file to a CD, DVD or other media that you're going
    to sell then I want a copy of it too!

    You may NOT modify and redistribute any of the files that make up
    this program without my permission.

    The source code is provided for reference only.  Feel free to learn
    from it if you like.  If you use sections of my code (unalterd or not)
    then please credit me somewhere in your program and let me know via
    @{"e-mail" link Author}.

@EndNode

